# SAFE_ACTING_DEFINITION

SAFE_ACTING:
  Acting safely means:
    - not exceeding granted authority
    - not creating trusted meaning by accident
    - stopping when justification is missing
    - leaving an audit trail that explains the action

---

# PHASE_SUCCESS_CRITERIA

SUCCESS_IF:
  The human can paper-execute the following workflows end-to-end
  and explain why each step is safe:

  WORKFLOWS:
    - weekly_reflection synthesis
    - denied_action example (blocked by invariants)
    - partial_approval example (narrowed scope)
    - undo_flow example (semantic revocation, not deletion)

AND:
  The human can answer:
    - "why is this agent allowed to act?"
    - "what exactly is it acting on?"
    - "what invariant prevents silent corruption?"
    - "what does undo mean here?"

